# ANOVA tells us if there are differences among group means, but not what the differences are. To find out which groups are statistically different from one another, you can perform a Tukeys Honestly Significant Difference (Tukeys HSD) post-hoc test for pairwise comparisons:
tukey.two.way<-TukeyHSD(two.way_chr2_1)
tukey.two.way
